So I'd select the text,
just go up to the toolbar

00:57:13.040 --> 00:57:14.980
and click on the link tool.

00:57:15.400 --> 00:57:18.020
And you'll notice a few things.

00:57:18.020 --> 00:57:21.510
So first, we give you a list of existing
pages that are already in the wikis.

00:57:21.560 --> 00:57:24.700
If I wanted to-- oh,
and I did accidentally--

00:57:25.560 --> 00:57:28.750
I can just click on one of those
pages and it'll create a live link.

00:57:28.910 --> 00:57:33.300
So let me get back to where I was.

00:57:39.620 --> 00:57:40.500
Oops.

00:57:40.500 --> 00:57:41.570
Select that text.

00:57:41.580 --> 00:57:43.060
Go back up here.

00:57:43.060 --> 00:57:46.680
Keep my hand off of the
keyboard or off the mouse.

00:57:46.680 --> 00:57:49.080
So we're showing at the top here
pages that have matching tags.

00:57:49.080 --> 00:57:50.500
And I'll talk a little
bit about tags later.

00:57:50.500 --> 00:57:52.380
But basically,
it's showing me the pages that

00:57:52.380 --> 00:57:56.170
are probably related to this.

00:57:56.390 --> 00:58:00.510
The page I'm about,
or to the page I'm typing on right now,

00:58:00.510 --> 00:58:02.060
also shows me recently viewed things.

00:58:02.060 --> 00:58:03.420
We feel that when you're
building out a wiki,

00:58:03.420 --> 00:58:05.930
the things you've viewed recently
are probably the things you

00:58:05.930 --> 00:58:07.300
want to link together later.

00:58:07.300 --> 00:58:10.710
I can also type in just a raw URL at
the bottom if I wanted to link to

00:58:10.710 --> 00:58:14.570
