00:58:16.660 --> 00:58:18.560
and this is really important in wikis.

00:58:18.560 --> 00:58:21.590
So one of the beautiful things about
a wiki is as you're editing content,

00:58:21.590 --> 00:58:25.440
you can very quickly put
placeholders in for pages that

00:58:25.450 --> 00:58:26.320
you're going to go fill out later.

00:58:26.320 --> 00:58:29.320
And that's what this new
page setting allows me to do.

00:58:29.320 --> 00:58:31.020
So I'm going to create the new page.

00:58:31.040 --> 00:58:32.780
Page has been created.

00:58:32.780 --> 00:58:37.340
I'm still editing my existing content.

00:58:37.390 --> 00:58:38.840
I will fix my spelling error.

00:58:38.840 --> 00:58:42.540
I click done, and I've now got a link.

00:58:42.560 --> 00:58:43.940
So links are very, very easy.

00:58:43.940 --> 00:58:48.500
I'm going to pop over to that link and
maybe now add some content to that page.

00:58:48.560 --> 00:58:50.050
page.

00:58:51.070 --> 00:58:53.100
So let me select that text.

00:58:53.100 --> 00:58:58.050
