We also show history.

01:01:06.700 --> 01:01:07.340
It's very nice.

01:01:07.340 --> 01:01:11.070
You can go back and look at
prior versions very quickly.

01:01:13.260 --> 01:01:15.540
Done with that.

01:01:15.550 --> 01:01:17.860
And the last thing I wanted
to talk about is tags.

01:01:17.860 --> 01:01:20.440
So one of the problems-- one of
the great things about wikis,

01:01:20.440 --> 01:01:25.660
actually, is that they're all about
organically creating content,

01:01:25.680 --> 01:01:28.600
linking that content together,
and making it possible to search

01:01:28.650 --> 01:01:31.560
across all of that content really,
really easily.

01:01:31.560 --> 01:01:33.670
I think that's great,
but we wanted to add a little

01:01:33.670 --> 01:01:34.860
bit more structure to that.

01:01:34.860 --> 01:01:36.890
So we added tagging.

01:01:36.910 --> 01:01:38.220
We don't have any tag clouds.

01:01:38.220 --> 01:01:41.100
I apologize to anybody
who's waiting for that.

01:01:41.600 --> 01:01:42.660
And tabs are easy.

01:01:42.660 --> 01:01:46.050
Just go up into the tag bar up here,
type your tag, hit Tab,

01:01:46.110 --> 01:01:49.750
go to the next tag.

01:01:56.500 --> 01:01:58.930
In there, if I want to remove a tag,
I can just take it and

01:01:58.930 --> 01:02:00.380
drag it off of the tag bar.

01:02:00.530 --> 01:02:02.540
Very, very simple.

01:02:06.820 --> 01:02:08.740
